OL,6,F"But fundamentally, we're still not
OL,7,Foverly happy with the CPS and the CQC
OL,8,Fjudgements on the apportion of the
OL,9,Fblame, and whether or not they had
OL,10,Fcases that they could prosecute fully
OL,11,Fin court".
OL,13,FHowever, Mr Koch praised the coroner
OL,14,Ffor her handling of the inquest.
OL,16,F"I think she's been very sensitive to
OL,17,Fall families concerned, and in the
OL,18,Fvery final stages of her deliberations
OL,19,Fshe came up with some very helpful
OL,20,Fpoints for the families," he said.
